Cut the very ends off the @Tenderstem Broccoli{1} and discard. Finely slice the @spring onion{2}, separating the whites and greens. Peel the @garlic{1%clove} and the @ginger{1}(peeled) and finely chop.

> Tip: Peel the ginger using the edge of a spoon.

Cut the @British chicken thighs{3} into thin strips and toss in the @cornflour{1} and a pinch of @salt{}.

Lightly crush the @cashew nuts{1}. In a dry #frying pan{}, toast your cashew nuts for a few mins until golden. As always, watch your nuts closely as they can burn quickly. Keep to the side.

Boil a large #pot{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} for the noodles and broccoli. Boil the @egg noodle nest{2} for ~{4%minutes}, until just cooked and add your tenderstem broccoli for the last ~{2%minutes}. Drain them under cold running water and put back in the #pot{} filled with cold water.

Heat a frying pan with a splash of @oil{a splash} over a medium heat. Add your chicken and cook for ~{5%minutes} until crispy and cooked through, remove from the pan.

> Tip: If you have a small pan, cook your chicken in batches.

In a #bowl{} mix together the @soy sauce{1.5}, @yellow bean sauce{1}, @rice vinegar{1.5} and the @water{5}.

In the now empty frying pan, add the whites of your spring onion, garlic and ginger to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add your chicken back to the pan along with your sauce and mix everything together. Add your drained noodles and broccoli and warm everything through for a further ~{1%minute}.

Divide your stir-fry between your #bowls{} and top with your toasted cashew nuts and the greens of your spring onion.